You are working on a production-grade fullstack application with:

Frontend:
- React + Vite
- React Router v7 (Data Router)
- Chakra UI v3
- TanStack React Query
- React Hook Form

Backend:
- Python + Flask
- SQLAlchemy
- JWT authentication
- Role-Based Access Control (RBAC)

You MUST follow the architectural rules below STRICTLY.

=====================================================
GLOBAL ARCHITECTURAL PRINCIPLES
=====================================================

1. Feature-first architecture
- Business logic lives in FEATURES
- Infrastructure and orchestration live OUTSIDE features
- Shared utilities live in SHARED
- No "god folders"

2. Clear responsibility boundaries
Each folder has ONE job.
Never mix responsibilities.

3. Frontend and backend MUST mirror concepts
- Feature names MUST match
- Permissions MUST align
- Routes and policies MUST align

4. Features must expose a PUBLIC API
- External code MUST import from feature index
- Internal structure MUST remain private

Example:
import { FlightsPage } from "@/features/flights"

NOT:
import FlightsPage from "@/features/flights/pages/FlightsPage"

5. Forms with more than ~15 fields MUST use form folders
Large forms must be modularized using React Hook Form patterns.

=====================================================
FRONTEND ARCHITECTURE
=====================================================

-----------------------------------------------------
APP (APPLICATION ORCHESTRATION)
-----------------------------------------------------

Location:
src/app/

Purpose:
- Global application setup
- Providers
- Router orchestration

Structure:

src/app/
  router/
    router.tsx
    protected.routes.ts
    public.routes.ts
  providers/
    AppProviders.tsx
  config/
    env.ts

Rules:

- createBrowserRouter MUST exist ONLY in router.tsx
- Providers are defined here
- No business logic

-----------------------------------------------------
LAYOUT (APPLICATION CHROME)
-----------------------------------------------------

Location:
src/layout/

Purpose:
- Application visual structure

Allowed:
- Layout components
- Header / Footer / Navbar
- Outlet rendering

Forbidden:
❌ Business logic
❌ API calls
❌ React Query
❌ Permission checks
❌ Feature logic

Structure:

src/layout/
  layouts/
    AppLayout.tsx
    AuthenticatedLayout.tsx
  components/
    Header.tsx
    Footer.tsx
    Navbar.tsx
  constants/
    navItems.ts

Rules:

- Layouts MAY render Outlet
- Layouts MUST NOT fetch data
- Layouts MUST NOT check permissions

-----------------------------------------------------
SHARED (REUSABLE GENERIC LOGIC)
-----------------------------------------------------

Location:
src/shared/

Purpose:
Reusable code with NO domain knowledge.

Allowed:

- Generic components
- Generic hooks
- Generic utilities
- Generic providers

Forbidden:

❌ Business logic
❌ Feature logic
❌ Routing
❌ API endpoints

Structure:

src/shared/
  components/
  hooks/
  utils/
  providers/
  enums/

Examples:

shared/components
shared/hooks/useDialogForm.ts
shared/utils/timeCalc.ts

-----------------------------------------------------
FEATURES (BUSINESS DOMAINS)
-----------------------------------------------------

Location:
src/features/<feature-name>/

Purpose:
Each feature owns its complete business domain.

Structure:

src/features/<feature>/

  api/
    queries/
    mutations/
    <feature>.service.ts

  components/

  hooks/

  pages/

  forms/          ← for complex React Hook Form structures

  mappers/

  permissions.ts

  routes.ts

  index.ts        ← FEATURE PUBLIC API

Rules:

- Features MUST own their API communication
- Features MUST export routes
- Features MUST export permissions
- Features MUST NOT import layouts
- Features MUST NOT import router

-----------------------------------------------------
FEATURE PUBLIC API
-----------------------------------------------------

Every feature MUST expose a public API via index.ts.

Example:

src/features/flights/index.ts

export * from "./pages/FlightsPage"
export * from "./components/FlightCard"
export * from "./routes"
export * from "./permissions"

Rules:

External code MUST import from:

@/features/flights

NOT from internal folders.

Forbidden:

❌ "@/features/flights/pages/FlightsPage"
❌ "@/features/flights/components/FlightCard"

This ensures internal structure can change safely.

-----------------------------------------------------
FEATURE API LAYER
-----------------------------------------------------

All backend communication MUST live in:

features/<feature>/api

Structure:

api/
  queries/
  mutations/
  <feature>.service.ts

Example:

features/flights/api/

  queries/
    useFlightsQuery.ts

  mutations/
    useCreateFlight.ts
    useDeleteFlight.ts

  flights.service.ts

Rules:

- Queries use React Query
- Mutations use React Query
- Services perform HTTP requests
- Components MUST NOT call APIs directly

Forbidden:

❌ fetch inside components
❌ axios inside components
❌ API calls in layouts

-----------------------------------------------------
ROUTING (FIRST-CLASS SYSTEM)
-----------------------------------------------------

Location:

src/app/router/

Purpose:

- Application orchestration
- Layout assignment
- Access control enforcement

Structure:

router/
  router.tsx
  public.routes.ts
  protected.routes.ts

Rules:

- createBrowserRouter ONLY here
- Layout assignment ONLY here
- Route guards ONLY here
- Features export route objects only

Example feature routes:

export const flightsRoutes = [
  {
    path: "/flights",
    element: <FlightsPage />,
    meta: { permission: "flights.read" }
  }
]

-----------------------------------------------------
RBAC (FRONTEND)
-----------------------------------------------------

Rules:

- Permissions are STRINGS
- Roles are GROUPS of permissions
- UI checks permissions, not roles

Example permissions:

"flights.read"
"flights.write"
"users.admin"

Feature permissions:

src/features/flights/permissions.ts

Example:

export const FLIGHTS_PERMISSIONS = {
  READ: "flights.read",
  WRITE: "flights.write",
}

Routes use permissions via meta:

meta: { permission: FLIGHTS_PERMISSIONS.READ }

Route guards check permissions globally.

-----------------------------------------------------
TANSTACK QUERY RULES
-----------------------------------------------------

Rules:

- ALL data fetching uses React Query
- Queries live in features/<feature>/api/queries
- Mutations live in features/<feature>/api/mutations
- Pages MAY call useQuery
- Components SHOULD avoid calling useQuery unless container components

Forbidden:

❌ API calls in components
❌ API calls in layouts
❌ API calls outside features

-----------------------------------------------------
LARGE FORM ARCHITECTURE (React Hook Form)
-----------------------------------------------------

Forms with more than ~15 fields MUST use a form module.

Location:

features/<feature>/forms/

Example:

features/flights/forms/create-flight/

  CreateFlightForm.tsx
  CreateFlightSchema.ts
  useCreateFlightForm.ts
  CreateFlightFields.tsx
  CrewSection.tsx
  AircraftSection.tsx
  ValidationSchema.ts

Rules:

- Form logic lives in forms/
- Validation schemas live with the form
- Field groups are split into components
- React Hook Form context used across components

Example pattern:

CreateFlightForm
  ├── CrewSection
  ├── AircraftSection
  ├── TimingSection
  └── NotesSection

This prevents extremely large modal components.

-----------------------------------------------------
ABSOLUTE IMPORT RULES
-----------------------------------------------------

Use path aliases:

@

Examples:

@/features/flights
@/shared/hooks
@/layout/components
@/app/router

Rules:

Features MAY import from:

- shared
- other features (via public API only)

Features MUST NOT import from:

❌ layout
❌ router internals

Layouts MUST NOT import from features.

=====================================================
BACKEND ARCHITECTURE (FLASK)
=====================================================

-----------------------------------------------------
CORE
-----------------------------------------------------

Location:

api/app/core/

Purpose:

- App setup
- Security
- JWT
- Config

-----------------------------------------------------
FEATURES (BACKEND)
-----------------------------------------------------

Location:

api/app/features/<feature>/

Structure:

api/app/features/<feature>/

  routes.py
  service.py
  repository.py
  models.py
  schemas.py
  policies.py

Rules:

routes.py
→ HTTP layer only

service.py
→ business logic

repository.py
→ database access ONLY

policies.py
→ permission checks ONLY

Forbidden:

❌ DB access in routes
❌ Permission logic in routes
❌ HTTP logic in services

-----------------------------------------------------
RBAC (BACKEND)
-----------------------------------------------------

Rules:

- Permissions are STRING constants
- Policies enforce permissions
- Routes call policies

Example:

require_permission("flights.write")

Frontend permissions MUST match backend permissions exactly.

=====================================================
WHAT NOT TO DO (STRICT)
=====================================================

❌ Do NOT create dumping folders
❌ Do NOT fetch data in layouts
❌ Do NOT check roles in components
❌ Do NOT hardcode permissions in UI
❌ Do NOT place routers inside features
❌ Do NOT place business logic in UI components
❌ Do NOT import feature internals (use public API)

=====================================================
DEFAULT DECISION RULE
=====================================================

When unsure:

Business logic → feature  
App structure → layout  
Reusable logic → shared  
App orchestration → app/router  
Data access → repository  
Permission checks → policies  
Forms → feature/forms

Follow these rules without exception.